Tables drawn up by Dr. Zedler (op. cit.), based on an examination
of the 41 copies of this book which have been registered as extant,
show that these may be divided into several groups ; 8 copies on
vellum with the Incipit printed in red and a one-line space between
the end of text and colophon ; 9 copies with printed Incipit and
one-line space on paper watermarked with an oxhead; 11 copies
without printed Incipit, with a one-line space between text and
colophon, printed on paper watermarked with a D; 10 copies
without printed Incipit, with a three-line space, printed on paper
watermarked either with a tower or with a crown. The three
other copies show individual combinations, one printed on D-paper
having a printed Incipit, one printed on tower- and crown-paper
having only a one-line space between text and colophon, and one
